# Changelog
All notable changes to local_catalog_browser will be documented in this file.

## [1.0.0] - 2026-03-08

### Added
- Initial release
- Course filtering by custom field values (text, select, checkbox, number, textarea)
- Course title filter with AJAX autocomplete suggestions (optional, enabled by default)
- Native Moodle tag filter with pill-based selector and dropdown autocomplete (optional, enabled by default)
- Filter by Moodle course category (optional, enabled by default)
- Dynamic AJAX search: results update without page reload as filters change
- Sort results by alphabetical order (A→Z), most recently created, or default Moodle order
- Paginated results with configurable page size
- Course cards displaying overview image, tags, and truncated summary
- Course preview page for non-logged-in users when guest access is enabled, with full description, tags, and back-to-catalog navigation preserving filters and pagination state
- Authenticated users are redirected directly to the course page if enrolled, or to the Moodle enrolment page if not — access and enrolment handled natively by Moodle
- Reset button to clear all active filters
- Keyboard navigation in all autocomplete dropdowns (arrow keys, Enter, Escape)
- Autocomplete suggestions limited to 10 results per query
- Only visible courses are returned in search results
- Custom fields with visibility set to "Nobody" are excluded from filters
- Placeholder text generated from custom field description, with fallback to field name
- Plugin settings: custom field category selector, title/category/tag filter toggles, configurable tag selection limit (1–25), results per page, guest access toggle
- Guest access toggle automatically syncs the guest role capability at system context
- Catalog page URL displayed in plugin settings for easy access and sharing
- English language strings included (French translation will be available via AMOS)
- Capability `local/catalog_browser:view` with default access for all authenticated user roles